    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're creating a game where each player starts at a certain level. Your program needs to remember the player's starting level when they begin the game.\r\n\r\n1. Create a variable called `starting_level`\r\n\r\n2. Assign it a number like `1` or `3`\r\n\r\n3. Use `print()` to display a message like\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   Starting at level 1\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can use **commas** in a `print()` statement to combine text and variables. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\nprint(\"Name:\", first_name)\r\n```",
